      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user is asking me to investigate a Blue Screen of Death (BSOD) error with stop code \"WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR\". They want me to:\n\n1. Investigate using enterprise root cause analysis\n2. Provide a fixability score using iFix (probably meaning I need to assess how fixable this is)\n3. Assess reliability and whether they can improve PC temperature\n4. They want to use PowerShell or Python tools (not stress testing components)\n\nLet me first analyze the error from the image:\n- Stop code: WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR\n- This is a hardware-related error (WHEA = Windows Hardware Error Architecture)\n- Common causes: CPU/GPU overclocking, unstable voltage, RAM issues, driver problems, or actual hardware failure\n\nSince I'm in a CLI environment with PowerShell available, I can:\n1. Check system information\n2. Check event logs for related errors\n3. Check temperatures if possible\n4. Check for any recent driver changesLet me start by gathering system information and checking event logs.",
      "timestamp": 1783146199219
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "bash",
      "code": "{\"command\": \"Get-WinEvent -FilterHashtable @{LogName='System'; Level=1,2; StartTime=(Get-Date).AddDays(-7)} -MaxEvents 50 | Where-Object {$_.Message -match 'WHEA|Hardware|Correctable|Uncorrectable'} | Select-Object TimeCreated, Id, LevelDisplayName, Message | Format-List\", \"description\": \"Check system event logs for hardware errors\"}",
